title: very minor wiki documentation clarification: long vs lon
body:
by **shawn.milo**: 
In this wiki page:
https://code.google.com/p/go-wiki/wiki/CodeReviewComments

This line appears:
func (f *Foo) Location() (lat, long float64, err error)

It is valid. However, "long" is being incorrectly highlighted, causing
confusion.

Renaming the variable to "lon" would fix it.
